["1. The first step in migrating Java EE code to Quarkus is to update the import statements from `javax.persistence` to `jakarta.persistence`. This is because Quarkus uses the Jakarta EE API, which has renamed the package names from `javax` to `jakarta`. This change is required to ensure that the code is compatible with Quarkus.\n\n2. The next step is to update the `pom.xml` file to include the necessary Quarkus dependencies. In this case, we need to add the following dependencies:\n\n```xml\n<dependency>\n    <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    <artifactId>quarkus-jakarta-persistence-api</artifactId>\n</dependency>\n<dependency>\n    <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache</artifactId>\n</dependency>\n```\n\nThese dependencies provide the necessary implementations for the Jakarta Persistence API and Hibernate ORM, which is used for database access in Quarkus.\n\n3. We also need to update the `persistence.xml` file to use the Quarkus-specific configuration properties. Specifically, we need to update the `hibernate.connection.datasource` property to use the Quarkus-specific `quarkus.datasource.jdbc-url` property.\n\n4. Finally, we need to update the `src/main/resources/application.properties` file to include the necessary configuration properties for the database connection. For example:\n\n```properties\nquarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\nquarkus.datasource.jdbc-url=jdbc:h2:mem:test\n```\n\nThese properties configure the H2 in-memory database for use in development mode."]